title: An introduction to the isatabr package
text: isatabr package developed easy--use package reading, modifying writing files Investigation/Study/Assay (ISA) Abstract Model metadata framework using ISA tab-delimited (TAB) format. ISA metadata framework manage increasingly diverse set life science, environmental biomedical experiments employ one combination technologies. Built around Investigation (project context), Study (unit research) Assay (analytical measurements) concepts, ISA helps provide rich descriptions experimental metadata (.e. sample characteristics, technology measurement types, sample--data relationships) resulting data discoveries reproducible reusable.

title: An introduction to the isatabr package
text: ISA-Tab structure described full detail ISA-tab website. description mostly taken slightly condensed appropriate. ISA-Tab uses three types file capture experimental metadata: Investigation file Study file Assay file (associated data files) Investigation file contains information needed understand overall goals means used experiment; experimental steps (sequences events) described Study Assay file(s). Investigation file may one Studies defined corresponding Study file; Study may one Assays defined corresponding Assay files. order facilitate identification ISA-Tab component files, specific naming patterns followed: i_*.txt identifying Investigation file, e.g. i_investigation.txt s_*.txt identifying Study file(s), e.g. s_gene_survey.txt a_*.txt identifying Assay file(s), e.g. a_transcription.txt

title: An introduction to the isatabr package
text: Investigation file fulfills four needs: declare key entities, factors, protocols, may referenced files; track provenance terminologies (controlled vocabularies ontologies) used, applicable; relate Study file Investigation (becomes necessary two Study files need grouped); relate Assay files Studies. Investigation file structured table vertical headings along first column, corresponding values subsequent columns. following section headings must appear Investigation file (order), study block (headings STUDY STUDY CONTACTS) can repeated, one block per study associated investigation. ONTOLOGY SOURCE REFERENCE INVESTIGATION INVESTIGATION PUBLICATIONS INVESTIGATION CONTACTS STUDY STUDY DESIGN DESCRIPTORS STUDY PUBLICATIONS STUDY FACTORS STUDY ASSAYS STUDY PROTOCOLS STUDY CONTACTS full description sections see aforementioned site.

title: An introduction to the isatabr package
text: Study file contains contextualizing information one assays, example; subjects studied; source(s); sampling methodology; characteristics; treatments manipulations performed prepare specimens.

title: An introduction to the isatabr package
text: Assay file represents portion experimental graph (.e., one part overall structure workflow); Assay file must contain assays type, defined type measurement (e.g. gene expression) technology employed (e.g. DNA microarray). Assay-related information includes protocols, additional information relating execution protocols references data files (whether raw derived).

what: Writing files in the ISA-Tab format.
title: An introduction to the isatabr package
text: updating ISA object, can written back directory using writeISAtab() function. content ISA object written investigation, study assay files following ISA-Tab standard file specification. default files written current working directory, directory can specified using path argument. Note existing files always overwritten. Therefore, writing files directory, original files read, result original files overwritten. Besides writing full ISA object also possible write investigation file , one study files one assay files.
code: ## Write content of ISA object to a temporary directory. writeISAtab(isaObject = isaObject1,              path = tempdir()) ## Write investigation file. writeInvestigationFile(isaObject = isaObject1,                        path = tempdir())  ## Write study file. writeStudyFiles(isaObject = isaObject1,                 studyFilenames = "s_study1.txt",                 path = tempdir())  ## Write assay file. writeAssayFiles(isaObject = isaObject1,                 assayFilenames = "a_study1.txt",                 path = tempdir())

title: isatabr package overview. — isatabr-package
text: isatabr package implementation ISA-Tab format R. builds R object ISA-Tab format files. ISA metadata framework manage increasingly diverse set life science, environmental biomedical experiments employ one combination technologies. Built around Investigation (project context), Study (unit research) Assay (analytical measurements) concepts, ISA helps provide rich descriptions experimental metadata (.e. sample characteristics, technology measurement types, sample--data relationships) resulting data discoveries reproducible reusable.

what: Check the validity of an object of class ISA. — validISAObject
title: Check the validity of an object of class ISA. — validISAObject
text: validISAObject function checks whether object class ISA valid object. object ISA considered valid : one investigation file, name starts i_ ends .txt, present folder containing ISA-Tab files. sections investigation file contain least columns specified specific section https://isa-specs.readthedocs.io/en/latest/isatab.html study assay files contain least columns specified https://isa-specs.readthedocs.io/en/latest/isatab.html

title: Check the validity of an object of class ISA. — validISAObject
code: validISAObject(object)

title: Check the validity of an object of class ISA. — validISAObject
text: object object class ISA.

title: Check the validity of an object of class ISA. — validISAObject
text: TRUE error message.

title: Check the validity of an object of class ISA. — validISAObject
code: ## Read example Atwell data set. isaObject1 <- readISATab(path = file.path(system.file("extdata/Atwell",                                           package = "isatabr")))  ## Check validity of the object. validISAObject(isaObject1)

title: Write ISA-Tab object. — writeISAtab
text: Write ISA-Tab object files. investigation file, study files assay files written folder specified path. also possible write investigation file, one study files, one assay files using respective functions.

title: Write ISA-Tab object. — writeISAtab
code: writeISAtab(isaObject, path = getwd())  writeInvestigationFile(isaObject, path = getwd())  writeStudyFiles(   isaObject,   studyFilenames = getStudyFileNames(isaObject),   path = getwd() )  writeAssayFiles(   isaObject,   assayFilenames = unlist(getAssayFileNames(isaObject)),   path = getwd() )

title: Write ISA-Tab object. — writeISAtab
text: isaObject object ISA-class. path character vector name directory file(s) written. default value current working directory. studyFilenames character vector indicating study files written. Default study files isaObject written. assayFilenames character vector indicating assay files written. Default assay files isaObject written.

title: Write ISA-Tab object. — writeISAtab
text: return value, files written path.

title: Write ISA-Tab object. — writeISAtab
code: ## Read example Atwell data set. isaObject1 <- readISATab(path = file.path(system.file("extdata/Atwell",                                           package = "isatabr")))  ## Write content of ISA object to a temporary directory. writeISAtab(isaObject = isaObject1,            path = tempdir())  ## Write investigation file to a temporary directory. writeInvestigationFile(isaObject = isaObject1,                        path = tempdir())  ## Write study file to a temporary directory. writeStudyFiles(isaObject = isaObject1,                 studyFilenames = "s_study1.txt",                 path = tempdir())  ## Write assay file to a temporary directory. writeAssayFiles(isaObject = isaObject1,                 assayFilenames = "a_study1.txt",                 path = tempdir())
